To fairly present the book value of the Road Networks account in the Financial Statements of the Municipality, we recommend that the Municipal Mayor direct the:

1. GSO and  the Municipal Engineer to conduct the physical inventory on the Local Road Network to come up with the Inventory Report on the Local Road Network.

2. GSO and the Municipal Engineer to evaluate the Local Road Inventory Report and reconcile with the accounting records to facilitate the reporting of the municipality’s road network system;

3. Municipal Accountant to adjust the books discrepancies noted;

4. Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the GSO-Designate with the complete description and cost segregation of the road components for road project.
